        public static double uniformDouble(double min,
                                   double max)
        from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/363681/generating-random-integers-in-a-range-with-java and http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3680637/how-to-generate-a-random-double-in-a-given-range Returns a pseudo-random number between min and max, inclusive. Uniform distribution. The difference between min and max can be at most Integer.MAX_VALUE - 1.
        Parameters:
        min - Minimum value
        max - Maximum value. Must be greater than min.
        Returns:
        Integer between min and max, inclusive.
        See Also:
        Random.nextInt(int)
